  <!-- UNDERSTANDING THE DESTINATION + PHOTO -->
  <section class="section section--white">
    <div class="section__inner">
      <div class="two-col-with-image">
        <div class="two-col-with-image__text">
          <h3>Understanding the Destination</h3>

          <p>
            <strong>Geography:</strong> The archipelago is split into two regencies:
            Banggai Kepulauan (Bangkep) and Banggai Laut (Balut).
            <strong>Peleng Island</strong> (Bangkep) is the massive island closest
            to the mainland-home to Lake Paisupok and most accommodation. <strong
              >Banggai Island</strong
            > (Balut) lies further south, the historical center of the Sultanate.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>Access:</strong> There is no airport on the islands. The gateway
            is <strong>Luwuk (LWK)</strong> on the Sulawesi mainland. Fly into Luwuk
            (via Makassar), taxi to the harbor, and ferry across to Leme-Leme on Peleng.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>The Budget Reality:</strong> Remote Indonesia is surprisingly
            expensive. Logistics cost money. Accommodation is cheap (250k-400k IDR),
            but transport kills the budget. A car charter is 700k IDR/day; boat charters
            run 800k-1.5m IDR. You need cash. ATMs are scarce outside Luwuk and Salakan.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="two-col-with-image__image">
          <Image
            src={coralReef}
            alt="Coastal waters of the Banggai Islands"
            widths={[400, 670]}
            sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 50vw"
            quality={50}
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

