       ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="section section--deep">
    <div class="section__inner">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-header__label">Practical Advice</span>
        <h2 class="section-header__title">What We Learned</h2>
        <p class="section-header__subtitle">
          Tips that make the difference between a tough trip and a memorable
          one.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="insider-grid">
        <div class="insider-card">
          <div class="insider-card__image">
            <Image src={mantaRays} alt="Dry bag for boats" />
          </div>
          <div class="insider-card__content">
            <h3 class="insider-card__title">Bring a Dry Bag</h3>
            <p class="insider-card__text">
              Between open boats, sudden downpours, and slippery docks, your
              gear will get wet. A 20L dry bag is essential for camera and
              passport.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="insider-card">
          <div class="insider-card__image">
            <Image src={softCoralMangrove} alt="Mosquito management" />
          </div>
          <div class="insider-card__content">
            <h3 class="insider-card__title">Mosquito Management</h3>
            <p class="insider-card__text">
              Dengue is a risk in Sulawesi. Mosquitoes in Luk Panenteng are
              aggressive at dusk. Burn coils, wear long linen; bring DEET-hard
              to find there.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="insider-card">
          <div class="insider-card__image">
            <Image src={wayagAerial} alt="Jam karet" />
          </div>
          <div class="insider-card__content">
            <h3 class="insider-card__title">"Rubber Time" (Jam Karet)</h3>
            <p class="insider-card__text">
              If a boat driver says 8:00 AM, he may mean he'll wake at 8, have
              coffee, buy fuel, and find you at 9:30. Do not plan tight
              connections.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="insider-card">
          <div class="insider-card__image">
            <Image src={karstTurquoise} alt="Snacks" />
          </div>
          <div class="insider-card__content">
            <h3 class="insider-card__title">Snacks Are Salvation</h3>
            <p class="insider-card__text">
              Food is repetitive. Village kiosks sell mostly sweet biscuits.
              Bring nuts, protein bars, or whatever comfort food you need.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="insider-card">
          <div class="insider-card__image">
            <Image src={heroPhinisi} alt="Snorkel gear" />
          </div>
          <div class="insider-card__content">
            <h3 class="insider-card__title">Snorkel Gear</h3>
            <p class="insider-card__text">
              Rental gear is often moldy, leaks, or has bitten-off mouthpieces.
              Bring your own mask and snorkel. Fins can be rented; mask is
              personal.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="insider-card">
          <div class="insider-card__image">
            <Image src={coralReef} alt="Waste" />
          </div>
          <div class="insider-card__content">
            <h3 class="insider-card__title">Waste</h3>
            <p class="insider-card__text">
              No formal trash disposal in villages. Carry plastic back to Luwuk.
              If you leave it in the village bin, it will likely be burned or
              dumped in the river.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

